snippet.textDisplay: My profound gratitude extends from the very depths of my heart to the esteemed Coke Studio Pakistan for bestowing upon us this ethereal and transcendental musical marvel. It is not merely a song; it transcends the realm of mere auditory stimulation to become an immersive experience, a journey through the corridors of emotion and sentiment. With each resounding note, a symphony of emotions reverberates within me—pain, joy, nostalgia—interwoven seamlessly into a tapestry of sound that captivates the soul. The melodic strains evoke a myriad of feelings, stirring the depths of my being and eliciting a profound resonance that lingers long after the final chord has faded into the ether. Indeed, the Coke Studio Pakistan's musical oeuvre is a testament to the profound power of art to encapsulate the human experience in all its complexity. It serves as a poignant reminder of the universal language of music, capable of transcending cultural divides and speaking directly to the soul. Thus, let my gratitude be expressed in the most profound terms, for this musical offering has enriched my life in ways immeasurable and ineffable. It is a treasure trove of emotion, a testament to the transformative power of music to elevate the spirit and awaken the senses to the beauty of the world around us.

Are the lyrics and translations going to be placed back on your website? Your songs always had translations not just in English but also in Urdu, which were of great benefit to the wider populace, especially in terms of familiarising them with regional tongues. Now its impossible to distill them seperately. Closed captions aren't even provided in Urdu as they were in the past. 

Hits like Pasoori could be read in 3 languages.
